706427f-a.text:
Avenue R, at the southeast corner of East 16th Street, showing Public School No. 234, also known as the School of Temple Ahavath Sholom of Flatbush. The synagogue is on the right. A new P.S. 234 was later built at Avenue S and East 17th Street.

Board of Education of the City of New York
Early 1930's
